<Window x:Class="danceoclock.HelpWindow"
        xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
        xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
        xmlns:d="http://schemas.microsoft.com/expression/blend/2008"
        xmlns:mc="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/markup-compatibility/2006"
        xmlns:local="clr-namespace:danceoclock"
        mc:Ignorable="d"
        Title="Help" Height="423.338" Width="831.214">
    <Grid Margin="0,0,5.667,31.667">
        <TextBlock HorizontalAlignment="Center" TextWrapping="Wrap" Width="802" Margin="10,60,9,-33.223" FontSize="14" Padding="10"><Run FontWeight="Bold" Text="1) Record a movement:"/><Run Text=" Press the &quot;Record Action&quot; button to record a wake-up routine. You can specify how long the routine is, and how often a frame is captured for matching upon performance. The recorded segment will be saved as a .txt file. The recording starts as soon as you are fully in frame of the Kinect camera, so be ready!"/><LineBreak/><Run FontWeight="Bold"/><LineBreak/><Run FontWeight="Bold" Text="Tips for recording movements: "/><Run Text="Make your movements simple for easy matching, and try to keep them facing the Kinect camera. The Kinect recognizes depth, so remember how you are angled away from the camera so you can match them later!"/><LineBreak/><Run/><LineBreak/><Run FontWeight="Bold" Text="2) Create an alarm: "/><Run Text="Press the &quot;New Alarm&quot; button to create an alarm for the near future, and select your music file (in the .mp3 format) and your previously recorded movement file. You may set the movement tolerance settings, the number of movement repititions you want to perform, and the maximum time spent on matching each frame. You also can select any alarm in the main menu and modify or delete them one by one."/><LineBreak/><Run/><LineBreak/><Run FontWeight="Bold" Text="3) Deactivate the alarm: "/><Run Text="When the time comes and the Dance O'Clock app is open on your computer, your music will play, and the Kinect's camera feed will be displayed. Get in the frame of the camera, and try to match the stick figure displayed. You may press the snooze button to delay the alarm by 5 minutes, but you can only do that three times."/></TextBlock>
        <TextBlock HorizontalAlignment="Center" TextWrapping="Wrap" VerticalAlignment="Top" Height="29" Margin="0,26,0,0" Width="821" TextAlignment="Center" FontSize="16"><Run FontWeight="Bold" Text="How to Use Dance O'Clock" TextDecorations="Underline"/></TextBlock>
    </Grid>
</Window>
